
(1) COMPILATION
(2) HOW TO BROWSE THE FILES
(3) CONTENT


(1) COMPILATION

THIS COQ THEORY COMPILES UNDER COQ 8.3pl5

  - create a Makefile by calling
     
      $ coq_makefile -f Make > Makefile
  
  - compile
    
      $ make

WARNING : the compilation of some of the files consumes up to
	  2GB of memory. make sure you dispose of sufficient 
	  reserves of ram before compiling the code.


(2) WORK WITH THE CODE

  - call COQIDE as follows from the root of the library 

      $ coqide -R . CatSem


(3) CONTENT

READ "./DESCRIPTION" FOR A DESCRIPTION OF THE CONTENT OF EACH FILE.
